      • containsKey

        boolean containsKey(Object key)
        Returns true if this map contains a mapping for the specified key. More formally, returns true if and only if this map contains a mapping for a key k such that (key==null ? k==null : key.equals(k)). (There can be at most one such mapping.)
        Parameters:
        key - key whose presence in this map is to be tested
        Returns:
        true if this map contains a mapping for the specified key
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified key is null

      • get

        Object get(String key)
        Returns the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this map contains no mapping for the key.

        More formally, if this map contains a mapping from a key k to a value v such that (key==null ? k==null : key.equals(k)), then this method returns v; otherwise it returns null. (There can be at most one such mapping.)

        Parameters:
        key - the key whose associated value is to be returned
        Returns:
        the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this map contains no mapping for the key
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified key is null

      • getBoolean

        boolean getBoolean(String key)
        Returns a boolean value from this options with the specified key. If the key contains another type of value, an IllegalArgumentException is raised. If the key does not exists in the configuration, then a false value is returned. Otherwise the stored configuration value is returned.
        Parameters:
        key - - the key whose associated Boolean value is to be returned
        Returns:
        the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this map contains no mapping for the key
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified key is null
        See Also:
        get(String, Class)

      • getString

        String getString(String key)
        Returns a string value from the configuration map with the specified key. If the key contains another type of value, an IllegalArgumentException is raised. If the key does not exists in the configuration, then null value is returned. Otherwise the stored configuration value is returned.
        Parameters:
        key - - the key whose associated String value is to be returned
        Returns:
        the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this map contains no mapping for the key
        See Also:
        get(String, Class)

      • getCollection

        <T> Collection<T> getCollection(String key,
                                Class<T> type)
        Returns a collection of values conform to the given class type found on the given key. If a single value (not a Collection) is mapped to the given key, then it wraps the value in a singleton set and returns it. Otherwise it tries to get the value as a Collection and return it.
        Parameters:
        key - - the key whose associated value is to be returned
        type - - the type of the items if a collection is mapped to the given key in this map
        Returns:
        a Collection mapped to the given key, or an empty collection if there was no mapping for the key, never null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - - if the elements in the collection is not applicable to the given type.

      • getList

        <T> List<T> getList(String key,
                    Class<T> type)
        Returns a list of values conform to the given class type found on the given key. If a single value (not a List) is mapped to the given key, then it wraps the value in a singleton list and returns it. Otherwise it tries to get the value as a List and return it.
        Parameters:
        key - - the key whose associated value is to be returned
        type - - the type of the items if a list is mapped to the given key in this map
        Returns:
        a List mapped to the given key, or an empty list if there was no mapping for the key, never null.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - - if the elements in the list is not applicable to the given type.

      • keySet

        Set<String> keySet()
        Returns a Set view of the keys contained in this map. The set is backed by the map, so changes to the map are reflected in the set, and vice-versa. If the map is modified while an iteration over the set is in progress (except through the iterator's own remove operation), the results of the iteration are undefined. The set supports element removal, which removes the corresponding mapping from the map, via the Iterator.remove, Set.remove, removeAll, retainAll, and clear operations. It does not support the add or addAll operations.
        Returns:
        a set view of the keys contained in this map
